title: Port Stanvac
notes:
Departed from O'Sullivans boat ramp near Port Stanvac.
Headed towards Port Noarlunga, trolled over Horseshoe Reef and caught 1 undersized snook, 1 legal snook and a nice Pike.

Headed towards Marino Rocks and berleyed up a school of Salmon which didn’t bite and caught the 2 squid, Tommy Ruff and Leatherjacket.

It was dead calm from about 1pm to 3pm then became very choppy.

- Fishing Partners - Me, Nick M, Chris P

- Nick M is a little retarded at knots!!!

- Low tide - 11:46pm High tide - 5:47

title: West Beach
notes: Took the boat out first time in 4 years. Tried a few spots around West Beach area and Brighton about 2-3kms out. Wasn't really expecting to catch too much or anything big, was just for some more experience from being off the water so long.

title: Coorong - Tauwitchere
notes:
Trolled around the end of Mundoo Channel and caught half a dozen salmon trout.

Went to Tauwitcheries in front of the sand dune "Secret Mulloway Spot" and caught plenty of salmon trout.
Ken caught a 33cm school mulloway on a fillet of salmon trout.

Moved further up the Coorong and caught more salmon trout but no luck of the mulloway.

Returned to the "Secret Mulloway Spot" near high tide about 6pm and school mulloway were on the run. Caught 4 schoolies, 2 on a 3" Fry Gulp on 2lb fireline.

title: Aldinga
notes:
Launched at Aldinga Beach and headed South towards the cliffs. Drifted around the rocks and pulled up a few squid, at the same time Billymako lost a tommy ruff on a soft plastic.
Eventually decided to make one of my famous rigs and caught a few leather jackets while drifting and using squid as bait.

title: Coorong - Sugars Beach
location: Coorong - Sugars Beach, South Australia, Australia
notes:
We fished the drop-off of a newly made channel created by the dredger across from Sugars beach. It is the 2nd hole from the mouth.

As soon as we arrived the school mulloway were on the bite, there weren't many salmon trout about. 
I hooked the first mulloway after my second cast.

Ken snapped his rod on the big flatty. We lost the anchor and broke the outboard cord. The girls brought down another anchor for us.

We then fished the top of the tide with less luck. Only hooked a nice salmon.

title: Coorong - Sugars Beach
location: Coorong - Sugars Beach, South Australia, Australia
notes:
We tried a few holes around the mouth but found that the holes with less current flow had the bigger salmon.

I hooked the school mulloway on a whole pilchard on a running sinker rig in the hole near the creek.

title: Coorong - Tauwitchere
notes:
Caught the school mulloway at Tauwitchere in front of the Hut/Shed area.

Fished the mouth on high slack tide.
Plenty of salmon around the mouth hole near the entrance.

High tide approx. 3pm in Victor Harbour.
Got to slack high tide approx. 5:30-6pm at the mouth.

title: Victor Harbour
notes:
- Not many fish around at all.

We tried the reef in front where we usually catch snook and didn’t get any hits.

Ken took his new Berkley combo out for the first time.

We then tried around Granite Island and Olivers Reef with no luck so we went down to Chiton Rocks where we only got one Tommy Ruff then went to Port Eliot where we got nothing.

- Ken stacked it at Chiton.

Next we went around Seal Rock with no luck and finally tried the reef next to Wright Island where we got 3 Tommy Ruff.

title: Reef
notes: fishing

title: Basham Beach
notes:
Fishing at Basham Beach today and landed this little bronzie using a whole small squid as bait using 2 x 9/0 Gamakatsu Octopus hooks and 4oz grapnel sinker.
Broke in my 13ft Daiwa Sensor which has a Saltiga Surf with 30lb Daiwa Saltiga Surf Braid.
The bait was about 60 metres out and the first run it tool striped about 100 metres of line. It took me around to the rocks but I muscled him back over to the beach.
We let him go to fight another day because we had no sharp filleting knives.

title: Basham Beach
notes:
Ken caught his first Mulloway with the moonraker.
It was very very windy until about 3pm.
The rod started to bounce on the 13ft Sensor Surf then I struck and hooked the Bronzie just as Ken and Joseph were walking onto the beach.
Ken went to the carpark to get food and to call Joseph just as he rode into the carpark and bumped into him.
We had a few other knocks throughout the day and the next day but nothing more.
I was using a 5.5oz grapnel sinker with twin 8/0 Gamakatsu Octopus hooks.

title: Watsons Gap
notes:
I went to Victor Harbor for the the long weekend and found a few nice looking spots. On the Sunday I caught a just legal mulloway around 8lb on a whole pilchard and we also landed 2 eagle rays.
Today we tried another new spot and landed 3 mulloway but they were all undersized.

We had to search for a gutter that didn't have any weed in it because there was plenty of weed around Victor this weekend.

* Owner 3-way swivel
* 2 x Gamakatsu octopus 8/0
* 80lb Black Magic Fluorocarbon leader

title: 42 Mile
notes:
Camped approx. 2kms right of 42 Mile entrance with Glenn, Ken, Fano and his cousin Chris.

Weed was annoying, disapeared for a few hours on the first night.

Fished a few hundred meters left of entrance next morning caught elephant sharks till weed also moved in.

Crossed Tea Tree after lunch through 1m of water, still weed everywhere.

title: Waitpinga Beach
notes:
Arrived at Waitpinga and used 4/0 Bleeding Pilchard Snapper Snatchers with squid and half pilchards as bait.
Caught 3 big salmon and plenty of salmon trout.
Ken caught a few big mullet also.
Ken broke the deck chair and landed flat on his back twice!!!

title: Waitpinga Beach
notes:
Used squid and pilchard pieces on a paternoster rig with circle hooks.
I was the only one to catch any fish out of Glenn, Ken and Courtney.
Many surfers were out, there was a competition on.
One surfer asked how we were going and I said we'd do better if there weren't any surfers out. He didn't look too happy.

title: Sellecks
notes:
We went out from Aldinga beach.
Dad got an $85 fine from council petrol for launching the boat in non-launch area.
Got the red mullet in about 15ft water with Read head Blade.
Dad caught the 2 squid.
Fished with Uncle Nick and Vasili also.

title: Henley Jetty
notes:
We ballooned out 2 whole squid.
The wind turned from S/E to West as we got the baits out.
We then waiting for the wind to turn and eventually put the baits back out around 2am with the wind tending S/W. Not very good conditions at all.
We caught a bucket full of crabs and people near the start of the jetty bagged out on yellow fin whitting.
Little fat kid and his friend were there talking about their chum.

title: Rapid bay
notes:
We camped at Rapid Bay overnight with Ian, Chris and Nik kef.

I caught 2 squid and Nik Kef caught 1 squid. 
We then cooked them on the BBQ with prawns.

We explored the caves and made a fake grave with sun glasses on the mound (need to check it out next time we camp there).

The boys made me jump off the rocks in my underwear and they said they would do the same but did not!

title: Coorong
notes:
We fished the Coorong with Ken, Dad, Steven and George.

We fished first at Tauwitchere. We only hooked up to a few small salmon trout. We had a couple of live baits out both under float and free swimming.

We then trolled around and fished up near the mouth for only a few small salmon trout.

Overall a very unproductive and slow day.

A jetskier splashed Dad, George and Steven in the boat with his jetski because he was trying to take out a mate's lures.

title: Chiton Rocks
notes:
Arrived at Chiton Rocks at 12.
Caught live mullet, tommy ruff and silver whiting.
I used a live mullet about 15cm long cast out into the hole.
I went up the hill to take a panoramic shot of the beach when the fish hit, Ken struck and I brought the fish in. Threw it back in because it was undersized.
Exact day last year in 2009 caught a legal fish up the beach at the gap.
Tide was incoming and the secret was fresh bait.
Also, lost 3 fish (suspected rays), me 2 and Ken 1.

title: Watsons Gap
notes: We went to fish Chiton rocks but was very weedy on arrival so we went to Watsons Gap. Live bait was hard to get on arrival. We fished in front of the river mouth. I caught a small mulloway on a small live tommy in about 1minute of casting. It was a very snaggy area so we moved to the next hole to the right of the mouth. Ken landed a small mulloway on live mullet and was also bitten of by a big fish. I hooked a massive eagle ray and landed it after a 20-30min fight.
